WEBVTT

00:05.798 --> 00:07.100
Dad: And the
interconnecting strands

00:07.133 --> 00:08.501
won't lose
their elasticity.

00:08.534 --> 00:10.503
And that's how you make
a homemade hairnet.

00:10.536 --> 00:12.072
Yeah, that's great, Dad.

00:12.105 --> 00:14.107
But what we asked was, "Why are
you wearing that helmet?"

00:14.140 --> 00:15.708
Oh, sorry,
I can't hear you that well.

00:15.741 --> 00:18.178
I'm wearing a helmet.
You're probably wondering why.

00:18.211 --> 00:20.280
You see, your mother
sent me to buy myself some

00:20.313 --> 00:22.983
exercise equipment, and I was
going to get an exercise bike,

00:23.016 --> 00:24.817
but I thought I'd need
a helmet first.

00:24.850 --> 00:26.519
For an exercise bike?

00:26.552 --> 00:28.254
No, for the exercise bike.

00:28.288 --> 00:29.956
I tried this one on,
and guess what?

00:29.990 --> 00:32.225
It was too small and you
couldn't take it off, so you had

00:32.258 --> 00:34.360
to buy it, or they wouldn't
let you leave the store?

00:34.394 --> 00:36.696
No. It was too small
so I couldn't take it off,

00:36.729 --> 00:39.966
and I had to buy it, or they
wouldn't let me leave the store.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.501
[ Remote clicks ]
Huh?

00:41.534 --> 00:42.735
[ Upbeat music plays on TV ]

00:42.768 --> 00:44.104
Ah!
What are you doing there?

00:44.137 --> 00:46.006
Sorry, that was getting
really annoying.

00:46.039 --> 00:47.907
Hmm.
So I can't hear very well,

00:47.940 --> 00:50.376
and I have extremely
limited peripheral vision.

00:50.410 --> 00:52.645
Do you kids want to hop in
the car and go for a drive?

00:52.678 --> 00:54.047
Absolutely not.

00:54.080 --> 00:55.982
Great!
Let's go grab some lunch!

00:56.016 --> 00:57.517
[ Screams, thudding ]

00:57.550 --> 00:58.751
Mind the Steps!

00:58.784 --> 01:00.586
Shouldn't we do
something about that?

01:00.620 --> 01:02.588
[ Loud clang ]
And the trash!

01:02.622 --> 01:05.458
Hmm, you're right.

01:05.491 --> 01:08.294
There.
Now we can hear the TV again.

01:08.328 --> 01:10.163
Dad: Hmm.
It's so quiet today.

01:10.196 --> 01:11.897
Hardly any traffic on the roads.

01:11.931 --> 01:13.499
[ Horns honking ]
[ Man screams ]

01:13.533 --> 01:15.435
Shame about all
these potholes, though.

01:15.468 --> 01:20.306
[ Gasps ] A parking spot right
outside Joyful Burger!

01:20.340 --> 01:22.242
[ Alarm blares ]

01:22.275 --> 01:24.377
[ Horns honking ]

01:24.410 --> 01:26.979
You kids wait here.
I'll get lunch.

01:27.013 --> 01:28.981
[ Sighs ]
For the last time, Bill,

01:29.015 --> 01:31.217
this is a bank
not a dating agency.

01:31.251 --> 01:32.985
Oh.

01:35.288 --> 01:36.256
[ Gasps ]

01:36.289 --> 01:38.258
Oh, my gosh,
this is really happening!

01:38.291 --> 01:39.325
[ Gasps ]

01:39.359 --> 01:40.993
Remember what they
told us, Larry --

01:41.027 --> 01:43.429
employees can be replaced,
money can't!

01:44.530 --> 01:45.831
Oh, forget the training!

01:45.865 --> 01:47.633
We're being robbed!
We're being Robbed!

01:47.667 --> 01:49.102
[ All gasp ]

01:49.135 --> 01:51.304
Hmm.
Must be someone's birthday.

01:51.337 --> 01:55.375
Everybody throw
your hands in the air!

01:55.408 --> 01:58.578
Okay.
You have a choice to make.

01:58.611 --> 02:01.947
Ah, heck, let's just make this
easy on both of us.

02:01.981 --> 02:03.383
I'll take everything
you've got.

02:03.416 --> 02:05.085
Uh, how do
you want that, sir?

02:05.118 --> 02:07.187
Uh, just in the normal
brown bags is fine.

02:07.220 --> 02:09.989
Don't be a hero, Larry!
I'm not being a hero!

02:10.022 --> 02:12.392
Just give him what he wants,
Larry, don't be hero!

02:12.425 --> 02:13.593
I'm not!

02:13.626 --> 02:16.196
[ Gasps ]

02:16.229 --> 02:19.332
♪♪

02:28.474 --> 02:29.575
[ Running footsteps ]

02:29.609 --> 02:31.944
[ Sighs ]
Okay, sir,
that's everything.

02:31.977 --> 02:34.046
Pleasure doing business
with you, gentlemen.

02:34.080 --> 02:36.015
Don't do it, Larry!
Don't press the alarm!

02:36.048 --> 02:37.517
Don't be a hero!

02:37.550 --> 02:39.919
What is your problem!?
What do you think you're doing?!

02:39.952 --> 02:42.155
Oh, yeah, that reminds me.

02:42.188 --> 02:44.056
We need to settle up.

02:44.090 --> 02:45.725
No, no, no!
Please don't!

02:45.758 --> 02:47.393
Okay!

02:47.427 --> 02:48.694
[ Door slams ]

02:48.728 --> 02:49.895
[ Sighs ]

02:49.929 --> 02:51.897
[ Alarm blares ]

02:51.931 --> 02:54.167
[ Horns honking ]
Dad: What a great day.

02:54.200 --> 02:56.336
We got a free lunch,
roads are all quiet.

02:56.369 --> 02:58.671
Even you two are behaving
yourselves.

02:58.704 --> 03:01.006
Man: So even though Larry is
screaming like a baby,

03:01.040 --> 03:02.575
I managed to keep a cool head.

03:02.608 --> 03:04.510
I said to the robber, "If you're
going to hurt these citizens,

03:04.544 --> 03:06.579
you're going to have
to come through me first."

03:06.612 --> 03:08.080
Wow, so brave.

03:08.114 --> 03:11.117
I'm gonna make sure the mayor
gives you a medal for this.

03:11.151 --> 03:12.685
Uh, that's not actually
what hap--

03:12.718 --> 03:14.854
Hey, we're gonna get to your
cowardly ramblings in a second.

03:14.887 --> 03:16.622
Don't let this man
bother you, sir.

03:16.656 --> 03:18.258
Please, continue.

03:18.291 --> 03:21.161
Then Larry handed over all
the money and the guy ran off.

03:21.194 --> 03:24.864
If you ask me, Larry was
a bit too cooperative.

03:24.897 --> 03:27.800
So you think this was
an inside job?

03:27.833 --> 03:29.935
Ah, what do I know?
I'm just a hero.

03:29.969 --> 03:32.872
I've heard enough.
Arrest this man!

03:32.905 --> 03:34.140
Case closed!

03:34.174 --> 03:35.975
Uh, Chief, we don't
have the money.

03:36.008 --> 03:37.577
Or the man who took it.

03:37.610 --> 03:39.912
I'm reopening the case.

03:39.945 --> 03:43.149
Okay, boys, I want roadblocks
here, here, and here.

03:43.183 --> 03:45.418
You do realize
that's a map of Paris.

03:45.451 --> 03:47.687
Like I said, we think he's gonna
skip the country,

03:47.720 --> 03:48.854
most likely to Paris.

03:48.888 --> 03:50.456
Beautiful city, Chief --
City of Love.

03:50.490 --> 03:52.525
Why aren't you out there
catching this guy?!

03:52.558 --> 03:56.095
Sir, please, don't make us give
you another full body search.

03:56.128 --> 03:58.464
Uh, Chief?
Take a look at the TV.

03:58.498 --> 03:59.965
[ Chuckles ]

03:59.999 --> 04:02.602
If its that video of the owl
riding the llama, I've seen it.

04:02.635 --> 04:03.869
No, that.

04:03.903 --> 04:05.271
Man: And now a breaking story.

04:05.305 --> 04:06.806
A bank robber
is making his getaway.

04:06.839 --> 04:09.375
Normally, we would call it
a high-speed police chase,

04:09.409 --> 04:11.744
but the police haven't really
started following him yet.

04:11.777 --> 04:14.113
So at the moment, it's more
of a leisurely drive.

04:14.146 --> 04:16.015
Can you guys believe
what's on TV?

04:16.048 --> 04:18.784
I know!
That owl is riding a llama!

04:18.818 --> 04:20.320
What a time
to be alive.

04:20.353 --> 04:22.655
No, you butt-clowns.
On Channel 6.

04:22.688 --> 04:24.524
Cool! Cool!

04:24.557 --> 04:26.992
Oh, I love these things!
Sometimes they get out and run.

04:27.026 --> 04:28.894
It's like, "Dude,
what are you doing?!"

04:28.928 --> 04:30.095
You're in a car!

04:30.129 --> 04:31.464
[ Gasps ]
That's our car!

04:31.497 --> 04:33.433
The bank robber
must have stolen it!

04:33.466 --> 04:35.034
Oh, I hope
Richard's okay!

04:35.067 --> 04:37.203
Uh, Mom,
that's Dad driving it.

04:37.237 --> 04:38.638
I'll kill him!

04:38.671 --> 04:40.906
Sheriff: Yes, sir, no one
is gonna get through

04:40.940 --> 04:42.342
a roadblock like this.

04:42.375 --> 04:44.977
[ Growls ] Why not build
the actual roadblock?!

04:45.010 --> 04:46.446
What would be the point
in spending

04:46.479 --> 04:48.348
all that taxpayer money
building the model

04:48.381 --> 04:49.982
if we're not
even going to use it?

04:50.015 --> 04:51.717
Then I'm not going
to pay my taxes.

04:51.751 --> 04:53.085
Really?
Boys!

04:53.118 --> 04:54.720
[ Screams ]

04:54.754 --> 04:56.956
Man: To give the illusion
of varied coverage,

04:56.989 --> 04:58.458
let's go to our man
in the street

04:58.491 --> 05:00.526
and get his eyewitness report.
Mike?

05:00.560 --> 05:03.863
Well, I'm at ground level, so I
can't really see anything.

05:03.896 --> 05:05.731
Uh, back to the chopper.

05:08.067 --> 05:10.102
And we've lost him.

05:10.135 --> 05:12.838
[ Tires screech ]

05:12.872 --> 05:15.275
[ Alarms blaring ]

05:17.410 --> 05:19.345
Dad: You'll never believe
what happened!

05:19.379 --> 05:20.946
I got us a free lunch!

05:20.980 --> 05:23.148
No, Richard,
you robbed a bank!

05:23.182 --> 05:24.884
Mom, he can't hear
with that thing on.

05:24.917 --> 05:26.486
[ Grunts ]

05:26.519 --> 05:29.322
It's all over the news!
It's on every channel!

05:29.355 --> 05:31.757
Really, for free burgers?
Slow news day.

05:31.791 --> 05:34.226
Richard, you didn't go
to Joyful Burger.

05:34.260 --> 05:36.996
You went to the bank,
and you stole $2 million.

05:37.029 --> 05:40.366
♪♪

05:40.400 --> 05:42.835
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my gosh!

05:42.868 --> 05:44.837
We have no lunch!

05:44.870 --> 05:46.306
[ Sobbing ]

05:46.339 --> 05:49.041
[ Sighs ]
We gotta return that money.

05:49.074 --> 05:51.577
But we're gonna need
to be clever about it.

05:53.913 --> 05:55.381
Taxi!

05:55.415 --> 05:57.317
[ Sighs ] Why didn't we use
a suitcase like that?

05:57.350 --> 05:58.684
This is all we had.

05:58.718 --> 06:00.486
Besides, I don't want
to give away a nice one.

06:00.520 --> 06:02.988
Richard, just go!
[ Whimpers ]

06:03.022 --> 06:04.957
Ah.
One thing.

06:04.990 --> 06:06.359
Good luck.

06:06.392 --> 06:08.027
[ Sighs ] It feels good
to do the right thing, Mom.

06:08.060 --> 06:10.396
I mean sure, that $2 million
could have paid off the house,

06:10.430 --> 06:12.765
our debt, and let you take
an early retirement, but --

06:12.798 --> 06:14.166
Mom: Somebody, stop him!

06:14.199 --> 06:17.102
Bring him down, bring him down!
Stop that man!

06:18.371 --> 06:21.341
-Oh, hi, Mr. Watterson!
-[ High-pitched ] Hi.

06:21.374 --> 06:23.343
[ Clears throat ]
I mean, hi.

06:25.144 --> 06:26.779
Say, I'd love
to stay and chat,

06:26.812 --> 06:29.014
but we're on the trail
of a bank robber.

06:29.048 --> 06:30.983
Oh, yeah.
I heard about that, ha.

06:31.016 --> 06:32.418
Maybe it was an accident?

06:32.452 --> 06:34.587
Accidental bank robbery?
That actually carries

06:34.620 --> 06:36.756
a higher jail time than
regular bank robberies.

06:36.789 --> 06:38.858
Hey, Earl, what we looking at
for accidental?

06:38.891 --> 06:40.560
Life -- at least.
And that's too good

06:40.593 --> 06:42.495
for 'em, if you ask me!
Am I right, fellas?!

06:42.528 --> 06:43.963
-Yeah, yeah, you're right!
-The worst!

06:43.996 --> 06:45.831
-I know, right?
-Don't even get me started!

06:45.865 --> 06:48.834
Anyway, what brings you here?

06:48.868 --> 06:50.703
[ Panting ]

06:50.736 --> 06:52.104
We need another plan.

06:52.137 --> 06:54.874
Uh, excuse me.
So sorry to interrupt.

06:54.907 --> 06:56.642
Uh, you forgot your...

06:56.676 --> 06:59.779
Here you go.

06:59.812 --> 07:02.214
Okay, well, uh...

07:02.247 --> 07:04.216
enjoy your alleyway.

07:04.249 --> 07:05.618
[ All exhale ]

07:05.651 --> 07:08.421
All right, here's the plan.
We do a heist.

07:08.454 --> 07:11.056
-Huh?!
-But in reverse.

07:11.090 --> 07:12.858
It's a normal day at the bank,

07:12.892 --> 07:15.761
and a mailman brings
a mysterious package.

07:15.795 --> 07:17.997
He takes it to an unsuspecting
Larry at the counter,

07:18.030 --> 07:20.199
who signs for it and reads
instructions telling him

07:20.232 --> 07:21.867
not to open it until
Christmas.

07:21.901 --> 07:24.670
Naturally, Larry would want
to keep the box safe.

07:24.704 --> 07:26.939
And where is safer
than the bank's vault?

07:26.972 --> 07:29.375
At the end of the day,
when everyone has left,

07:29.409 --> 07:31.411
I make my move.

07:33.212 --> 07:35.180
I make my way to
the safety deposit boxes,

07:35.214 --> 07:38.618
avoiding the high-tech state-
of-the-art security system.

07:40.319 --> 07:43.155
All I have to do is put
the money back.

07:43.188 --> 07:44.924
I put the money back...

07:44.957 --> 07:46.158
Really?

07:46.191 --> 07:48.494
I put the money back...

07:48.528 --> 07:50.195
in our account.
We purchase first-class

07:50.229 --> 07:52.432
one-way tickets to Martinique
and spend the rest of our lives

07:52.465 --> 07:54.033
living in sunshine
and total luxury!

07:54.066 --> 07:55.234
Mom!
Mom!
Mom!

07:55.267 --> 07:56.536
Should have seen
that coming.

07:56.569 --> 07:58.638
Ooh, ooh!
I've got one!

07:58.671 --> 08:01.674
It's the dead of night,
and I've got the cash.

08:01.707 --> 08:05.177
I go to an ATM, but instead
of taking money out,

08:05.210 --> 08:07.613
I put the money in.

08:10.416 --> 08:11.684
[ Siren wails ]

08:11.717 --> 08:14.386
Hold your horses,
bucky-o.

08:14.420 --> 08:17.523
I've been eyeballing you
cramming that there money box

08:17.557 --> 08:19.959
full of Benjamins for
the last three days.

08:19.992 --> 08:22.094
It's a first-class ticket
to the birdhouse for you.

08:22.127 --> 08:23.295
Kapoosh?

08:23.328 --> 08:25.297
-Birdhouse?
-Bucky-o?

08:25.330 --> 08:26.599
All: Kapoosh?!

08:26.632 --> 08:28.000
What?
That's how cops talk!

08:28.033 --> 08:29.435
No one speaks like that

08:29.469 --> 08:31.671
in this or any other branch
of reality, kapoosh?

08:31.704 --> 08:33.673
Agh!
Okay, here's what we do.

08:33.706 --> 08:36.041
We put the money back
from inside.

08:36.075 --> 08:39.445
You see, the bank accepts
one internship every year.

08:39.479 --> 08:41.547
I study to take
the financial services exam

08:41.581 --> 08:43.215
and pass
with distinction.

08:43.248 --> 08:44.517
Working weekends

08:44.550 --> 08:46.418
and taking every hour
of overtime available,

08:46.452 --> 08:48.621
I work my way up from
intern to assistant manager,

08:48.654 --> 08:50.355
assistant manager
to manager,

08:50.389 --> 08:52.324
and from manager
to regional manager.

08:52.357 --> 08:54.326
All I need to do then
is deposit a dollar a day

08:54.359 --> 08:55.628
into the bank's central account

08:55.661 --> 08:57.597
as an aggregated
transactional fee every day,

08:57.630 --> 08:58.831
thus returning the money.

08:58.864 --> 09:01.066
One single dollar
every single day.

09:01.100 --> 09:02.802
Practically undetectable.

09:02.835 --> 09:05.505
Gumball: Wait, giving back
$2 million one day at a time?

09:05.538 --> 09:09.174
Wouldn't you have to work there
for like...

09:09.208 --> 09:11.711
two m-mi-million days?

09:11.744 --> 09:14.714
Oh, yeah.

09:14.747 --> 09:16.716
No, wait --
I've got it!

09:16.749 --> 09:18.551
Just before
the police catch me,

09:18.584 --> 09:21.086
I manage to bury the money
somewhere no one will find it.

09:21.120 --> 09:24.156
And so I know where it is,
I leave myself a subtle clue.

09:24.189 --> 09:25.991
After being apprehended,
I'm sentenced

09:26.025 --> 09:28.360
to 20 years in
the state penitentiary.

09:28.393 --> 09:29.862
But I have a plan!

09:29.895 --> 09:31.897
I'm going to tunnel
my way out.

09:31.931 --> 09:35.467
Unfortunately, all they had in
the canteen was plastic forks.

09:35.501 --> 09:38.403
It took me 20 years,
but I was out.

09:38.437 --> 09:41.206
[ Grunting ]

09:41.240 --> 09:43.342
♪♪

09:46.946 --> 09:50.415
Then all I have to do
is collect the money.

09:50.449 --> 09:52.552
What the --

09:54.820 --> 09:56.989
[ Growls ]

09:57.022 --> 09:59.559
Hey?
What's going on?!

09:59.592 --> 10:02.461
Oh, Richard darling!
Mwah! Mwah!

10:02.494 --> 10:03.829
How lovely to see you.

10:03.863 --> 10:05.430
Did you spend
all the money?

10:05.464 --> 10:07.499
Well, it seemed rather
a shame not to.

10:07.533 --> 10:09.669
Yes, Papa, it wasn't even
earning interest.

10:09.702 --> 10:11.336
Wait, how did you know
where I hid it?

10:11.370 --> 10:12.938
Together: We're watching
your flash-forward.

10:12.972 --> 10:14.807
Oh, come on!
That doesn't seem fair!

10:14.840 --> 10:17.309
You did rob a bank.
Hmph!

10:17.342 --> 10:19.779
Darwin,
do you have an idea?

10:19.812 --> 10:21.180
Darwin?

10:21.213 --> 10:22.615
[ All gasp ]
I did it!

10:22.648 --> 10:24.516
I just dropped the money
back in the bank.

10:24.550 --> 10:25.885
Problem solved!

10:25.918 --> 10:28.087
We did it!
Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

10:28.120 --> 10:30.422
Uh, you guys are gonna
have to clear the area.

10:30.455 --> 10:32.658
We just found a suspicious
package in the bank!

10:32.692 --> 10:35.427
But don't worry, we're going
to do a controlled explosion!

10:35.460 --> 10:38.598
[ Explosion ]

10:38.631 --> 10:40.733
Well, we tried.

10:41.934 --> 10:44.704
[ Upbeat music plays ]
